Gor Mahia Secretary General Sam Ochola said Vaz Pinto who holds Uefa Pro and Caf 'A' coaching licences will hit the ground running upon arrival. 

"He is a good coach with all the credentials. After my handshake with the chairman (Ambrose Rachier) our focus now is to take the club forward and change the fortunes both on the pitch and management," Ochola told Nation Sport on Saturday. 

But even as the 46-year-old prepares to take over at the record Kenyan champions, he will have to dig deep to convince a section of Gor Mahia faithfuls who have expressed reservations due to his past record. 






Vaz Pinto has previously coached St George of Ethiopia and Angolan club Clube Recreativo Desportivo do Libolo. He also had a short stint at FC Famalicao Under-23 team in Portugal from September 2019 to June 2020. 

At FC Famalicao, Vaz Pinto won only four matches out of 26 he oversaw at the club. The tactician also served for only seven days at Ghanaian giants Heart of Oak after disagreeing with the management over realignment of technical bench. 

It's still not clear why Posta Rangers coach Sammy 'Pamzo' Omollo - who led Gor in Caf Champions League matches against APR of Rwanda and CR Belouizdad of Algeria - was not considered for the job. 



