Gor has been paired with Napsa Stars of Zambia in Caf Confederation Cup play-offs with K'Ogalo hosting the first leg on February 14 before travelling to Zambia for the second leg on February 21. 

Ochola has urged fans to give Vaz Pinto time to build a winning side. 

"He will be on the touchline on Sunday after arriving in the morning. He should start preparing the team for Caf and league matches. We are working on a solid management plan and early preparations for Caf matches and that is why we should give the new coach time to work," added Ochola. 

Gor has struggled to pay foreign coaches in the recent past forcing them to leave the club under unclear circumstances. 

Frank Nuttal, Dylan Kerr, Zdravcko Logarusic, Jose Marcelo Ferreira aka Ze Maria, Hassan Oktay and Steven Polack have all left in the past citing personal reasons and financial issues. 

It remains to be seen who the club will name as assistant coach after Patrick Odhiambo left K'Ogalo for a similar role at Bandari this week. He joins as a free agent having left Zesco United in December 2020. Caf Confederation Cup two-leg playoffs will be held between February 14 and 21. Experts say authorities may have destroyed or scrubbed away crucial evidence in a panicked initial response. The man who holds a Nigerian passport was on Friday night arrested in connection with a gruesome killing in Syokimau. Stephen Thuku was reportedly blocked by another car at Nairobi’s Githurai Mwihoko area by three armed men.